'''Wakamiya''' (若宮)  
{{TOCright}}  

== Imperial Household ==  
* A child of the {{ill|Imperial Family|ja|皇族}}. Refers to a {{ill|Prince|ja|皇子}} during their childhood.  
* Before {{ill|1947|ja|1947年}} ({{ill|Shōwa 22|ja|昭和22年}}), when the {{ill|Eleven Miyake|ja|旧皇族}} renounced their {{ill|Imperial status|ja|皇籍}}, it was customary to refer to the heir of a {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮家}} head (usually the eldest son) as "'''○○ Wakamiya''' (○○のわかみや)." <ref>May 4, 1895, Yomiuri Shimbun: "The 5th Selected Exhibition Awards Ceremony - Prizes Presented by Kitashirakawa Wakamiya Prince"</ref><ref>May 25, 1907, Asahi Shimbun: "Naming of Fushimi Wakamiya Royal Daughter"  
Here, "Fushimi Wakamiya" refers to Prince {{ill|Hiroyasu Fushimi|ja|伏見宮博恭王}} before inheriting the {{ill|Fushimi-no-miya|ja|伏見宮}} title. He succeeded the title in {{ill|1923|ja|1923年}}.</ref><ref>December 24, 1941, Yomiuri Shimbun: "Kitashirakawa Wakamiya attends the Children's Music Event"</ref>. According to this custom, Prince {{ill|Tomohito|ja|寬仁親王}}, the first son of {{ill|Prince Takahito of Mikasa|ja|三笠宮崇仁親王}}, would be "'''Mikasa Wakamiya'''", and Prince {{ill|Hisahito|ja|悠仁親王}}, the first son of {{ill|Prince Fumihito|ja|秋篠宮文仁親王}}, would be "'''Akishino Wakamiya'''." However, this designation is rarely used even among those knowledgeable about the {{ill|Imperial Household|ja|皇室}} system today. Instead, it is common to use the {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮号}} as if it were a {{ill|surname|ja|名字}}. Prince Tomohito expressed his criticism of this practice. {{main|{{ill|Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|ja|寬仁親王#宮号の有無と表記}}}}  

== Religion ==  
* A {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社}} enshrining the child ({{ill|Mikogami|ja|御子神}}) of the main deity ({{ill|Hongen|ja|本宮}}). Examples include various {{ill|Wakamiya Shrines|ja|若宮神社}} and {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrines|ja|若宮八幡宮}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Ōji|ja|若宮大路}} - The {{ill|approach|ja|参道}} to {{ill|Tsurugaoka Hachimangū|ja|鶴岡八幡宮}} in {{ill|Kamakura|ja|鎌倉市}}, {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|若宮神社 (曖昧さ回避)}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Sha (disambiguation)|ja|若宮社 (曖昧さ回避)}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|若宮八幡宮 (曖昧さ回避)}}  

== Place Names ==  
Japanese place names.  
* Wakamiya (Yamagata City) - A {{ill|locality|ja|地名}} in {{ill|Yamagata City|ja|山形市}}, {{ill|Yamagata Prefecture|ja|山形県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya (Nakano Ward)|ja|若宮 (中野区)}} - A locality in {{ill|Nakano Ward|ja|中野区}}, {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京都}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya (Okegawa City)|ja|若宮 (桶川市)}} - A locality in {{ill|Okegawa City|ja|桶川市}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya (Ichikawa City)|ja|若宮 (市川市)}} - A locality in {{ill|Ichikawa City|ja|市川市}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県}}.  
* Wakamiya (Ichihara City) - A locality in {{ill|Ichihara City|ja|市原市}}, Chiba Prefecture.  
* Wakamiya (Nagano City) - A locality in {{ill|Nagano City|ja|長野市}}, {{ill|Nagano Prefecture|ja|長野県}}. {{main|{{ill|Owabebe (Nagano City)#Wakamiya|ja|尾張部 (長野市)#若宮}}}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya (Kanazawa City)|ja|若宮 (金沢市)}} - A locality in {{ill|Kanazawa City|ja|金沢市}}, {{ill|Ishikawa Prefecture|ja|石川県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya (Saga City)|ja|若宮 (佐賀市)}} - A locality in {{ill|Saga City|ja|佐賀市}}, {{ill|Saga Prefecture|ja|佐賀県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya (Fukuoka City)|ja|若宮 (福岡市)}} - A locality in {{ill|Higashi Ward, Fukuoka City|ja|東区 (福岡市)}}, {{ill|Fukuoka City|ja|福岡市}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Town|ja|若宮町}} - A former municipality in {{ill|Kurate District|ja|鞍手郡}}, Fukuoka Prefecture, now part of {{ill|Miyawaka City|ja|宮若市}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Town (disambiguation)|ja|若宮町 (曖昧さ回避)}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Town (Kanazawa City)|ja|若宮町 (金沢市)}} - A locality in Kanazawa City, Ishikawa Prefecture.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Town (Nakamura Ward, Nagoya City)|ja|若宮町 (名古屋市中村区)}} - A locality in {{ill|Nakamura Ward, Nagoya City|ja|名古屋市中村区}}, {{ill|Nagoya City|ja|名古屋市}}.  
* Wakamiya Town (Yamaguchi City) - A locality in {{ill|Yamaguchi City|ja|山口市}}, {{ill|Yamaguchi Prefecture|ja|山口県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Village (disambiguation)|ja|若宮村 (曖昧さ回避)}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Island|ja|若宮島}} - An island in {{ill|Iki City|ja|壱岐市}}, {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya River|ja|若宮川}} - A {{ill|river|ja|河川}} in {{ill|Nihonmatsu City|ja|二本松市}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県}}.  

== Personal Names ==  
A Japanese {{ill|surname|ja|姓}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Clan|ja|若宮氏}}  
* {{ill|Hirofumi Wakamiya|ja|若宮啓文}} - Journalist.  
* {{ill|Teiko Wakamiya|ja|若宮テイ子}} - Disc jockey.  

== Transportation ==  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Interchange|ja|若宮出入口}} - An interchange on the {{ill|Hanshin Expressway Route 3 Kobe Line|ja|阪神高速3号神戸線}} in {{ill|Suma Ward, Kobe City|ja|須磨区}}, {{ill|Kobe City|ja|神戸市}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Boulevard|ja|若宮大通}} - A {{ill|100-meter road|ja|100m道路}} in {{ill|Nagoya City|ja|名古屋市}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Street|ja|若宮通}} - A north-south road in {{ill|Kyoto City|ja|京都市}}, {{ill|Kyoto Prefecture|ja|京都府}}.  

== Railway ==  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Station|ja|若宮駅}} - A station on the {{ill|JR Tadami Line|ja|只見線}} in {{ill|Aizubange Town|ja|会津坂下町}}, {{ill|Kawanuma District|ja|河沼郡}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県}}.  

== Military ==  
Japanese {{ill|Navy|ja|日本海軍}} warships or {{ill|Kaibokan|ja|海防艦}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya (Seaplane Tender)|ja|若宮 (水上機母艦)}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya (Kaibokan)|ja|若宮 (海防艦)}} <ref>The second Wakamiya, the 8th ship of the {{ill|Etorofu-class Kaibokan|ja|択捉型海防艦}}.</ref>  

