== Imperial Household == * A child of the {{ill|Imperial Family|ja|皇族}}. Refers to a {{ill|Prince|ja|皇子}} during their childhood. * Before {{ill|1947|ja|1947年}} ({{ill|Shōwa 22|ja|昭和22年}}), when the {{ill|Eleven Miyake|ja|旧皇族}} renounced their {{ill|Imperial status|ja|皇籍}}, it was customary to refer to the heir of a {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮家}} head (usually the eldest son) as "'''○○ Wa]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[ya''' (○○のわかみや)." <ref>May 4, 1895, Yomiuri Shimbun: "The 5th Selected Exhibition Awards Ceremony - Prizes Presented by Kitashirakawa Wa]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[ya Prince"</ref><ref>May 25, 1907, Asahi Shimbun: "Naming of Fushimi Wa]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[ya Royal Daughter" Here, "Fushimi Wa]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[ya" refers to Prince {{ill|Hiroyasu Fushimi|ja|伏見宮博恭王}} before inheriting the {{ill|Fushimi]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[miya|ja|伏見宮}} title. He succeeded the title in {{ill|1923|ja|1923年}}.</ref><ref>December 24, 1941, Yomiuri Shimbun: "Kitashirakawa Wa]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[ya attends the Children's Music Event"</ref>. According to this custom, Prince {{ill|Tomohito|ja|寬仁親王}}, the first son of {{ill|Prince Takahito of Mikasa|ja|三笠宮崇仁親王}}, would be "'''Mikasa Wa]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[ya'''", and Prince {{ill|Hisahito|ja|悠仁親王}}, the first son of {{ill|Prince Fumihito|ja|秋篠宮文仁親王}}, would be "'''Aki]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[o Wa]][[Category:Automatic wikipedia redirects to break]] [[Category:kkk]] [[ya'''." However, this designation is rarely used even among those knowledgeable about the {{ill|Imperial Household|ja|皇室}} system today. Instead, it is common to use the {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮