* A child of the {{ill|Imperial Family|ja|皇族}}. Refers to a {{ill|Imperial Prince|ja|皇子|vi|Hoàng tử|zh|皇子|ko|황자|lt=Imperial Prince}} during their childhood.  
* Before {{ill|1947|ja|1947th year }} ({{ill|Shōwa 22|ja|昭和22nd year }}), when the {{ill|Eleven Miyake|ja|旧皇族}} renounced their {{ill|Imperial status|ja|皇籍}}, it was customary to refer to the heir of a {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮家}} head (usually the eldest son) as "'''○○ Wakamiya''' (○○のわかみや)." <ref>May 4, 1895, Yomiuri Shimbun: "The 5th Selected Exhibition Awards Ceremony - Prizes Presented by Kitashirakawa Wakamiya Prince"</ref><ref>May 25, 1907, Asahi Shimbun: "Naming of Fushimi Wakamiya Royal Daughter"  
Here, "Fushimi Wakamiya" refers to Prince {{ill|Hiroyasu Fushimi|ja|伏見宮博恭王}} before inheriting the {{ill|Fushimi-no-miya|ja|伏見宮}} title. He succeeded the title in {{ill|1923|ja|1923rd year }}.</ref><ref>December 24, 1941, Yomiuri Shimbun: "Kitashirakawa Wakamiya attends the Children's Music Event"</ref>. According to this custom, Prince {{ill|Tomohito|ja|寬仁親王}}, the first son of {{ill|Prince Takahito of Mikasa|ja|三笠宮崇仁親王}}, would be "'''Mikasa Wakamiya'''", and Prince {{ill|Hisahito|ja|悠仁親王}}, the first son of {{ill|Prince Fumihito|ja|秋篠宮文仁親王}}, would be "'''Akishino Wakamiya'''." However, this designation is rarely used even among those knowledgeable about the {{ill|Imperial Household|ja|皇室}} system today. Instead, it is common to use the {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮号}} as if it were a {{ill|surname|ja|名字}}. Prince Tomohito expressed his criticism of this practice. {{main|{{ill|Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|ja|寬仁親王#宮号の有無と表記}}}}  

== Religion ==  
* A {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社}} enshrining the child ({{ill|Mikogami|ja|御子神}}) of the main deity ({{ill|Hongen|ja|本宮}}). Examples include various {{ill|Wakamiya Shrines|ja|若宮神社}} and {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrines|ja|若宮八幡宮}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Ōji|ja|若宮大路}} - The {{ill|approach|ja|参道}} to {{ill|Tsurugaoka Hachimangū|ja|鶴岡八幡宮}} in {{ill|Kamakura|ja|鎌倉市}}, {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|若宮神社 (曖昧さ回避)}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Sha (disambiguation)|ja|若宮社 (曖昧さ回避)}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|若宮八幡宮 (曖昧さ回避)}}  

