* Before {{ill|1947|ja|1947th year|12=draft}} ({{ill|Shōwa 22|ja|昭和22nd year|12=draft}}), when the {{ill|Eleven Miyake|ja|旧皇族|12=draft}} renounced their {{ill|Imperial status|ja|皇籍|12=draft}}, it was customary to refer to the heir of a {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮家|12=draft}} head (usually the eldest son) as "'''○○ Wakamiya''' (○○のわかみや)." <ref>May 4, 1895, Yomiuri Shimbun: "The 5th Selected Exhibition Awards Ceremony - Prizes Presented by Kitashirakawa Wakamiya Prince"</ref><ref>May 25, 1907, Asahi Shimbun: "Naming of Fushimi Wakamiya Royal Daughter"  
Here, "Fushimi Wakamiya" refers to Prince {{ill|Hiroyasu Fushimi|ja|伏見宮博恭王|12=draft}} before inheriting the {{ill|Fushimi-no-miya|ja|伏見宮|12=draft}} title. He succeeded the title in {{ill|1923|ja|1923rd year|12=draft}}.</ref><ref>December 24, 1941, Yomiuri Shimbun: "Kitashirakawa Wakamiya attends the Children's Music Event"</ref>. According to this custom, Prince {{ill|Tomohito|ja|寬仁親王|12=draft}}, the first son of {{ill|Prince Takahito of Mikasa|ja|三笠宮崇仁親王|12=draft}}, would be "'''Mikasa Wakamiya'''", and Prince {{ill|Hisahito|ja|悠仁親王|12=draft}}, the first son of {{ill|Prince Fumihito|ja|秋篠宮文仁親王|12=draft}}, would be "'''Akishino Wakamiya'''." However, this designation is rarely used even among those knowledgeable about the {{ill|Imperial Household|ja|皇室|12=draft}} system today. Instead, it is common to use the {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮号|12=draft}} as if it were a {{ill|surname|ja|名字|12=draft}}. Prince Tomohito expressed his criticism of this practice. {{main|{{ill|Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|ja|寬仁親王#宮号の有無と表記|12=draft}}}}  

== Religion ==  
* A {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} enshrining the child ({{ill|Mikogami|ja|御子神|12=draft}}) of the main deity ({{ill|Hongen|ja|本宮|12=draft}}). Examples include various {{ill|Wakamiya Shrines|ja|若宮神社|12=draft}} and {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrines|ja|若宮八幡宮|12=draft}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Ōji|ja|若宮大路|12=draft}} - The {{ill|approach|ja|参道|12=draft}} to {{ill|Tsurugaoka Hachimangū|ja|鶴岡八幡宮|12=draft}} in {{ill|Kamakura|ja|鎌倉市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県|12=draft}}.  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|若宮神社 (曖昧さ回避)|12=draft}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Sha (disambiguation)|ja|若宮社 (曖昧さ回避)|12=draft}}  
* {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|若宮八幡宮 (曖昧さ回避)|12=draft}}  

