== Imperial Household ==  
* A child of the {{ill|Imperial Family|ja|皇族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Family|qq=}}. Refers to a {{ill|Imperial Prince|ja|皇子|vi|Hoàng tử|zh|皇子|ko|황자|lt=Imperial Prince|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Prince|qq=}} during their childhood.  
* Before [[:en:1947|1947]] ({{ill|Shōwa 22|ja|昭和22年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōwa 22|qq=}}), when the [[:en:Ōke|Eleven Miyake]] renounced their {{ill|Imperial status|ja|皇籍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial status|qq=}}, it was customary to refer to the heir of a {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyake|qq=}} head (usually the eldest son) as "'''○○ Wakamiya''' (○○のわかみや)." <ref>May 4, 1895, Yomiuri Shimbun: "The 5th Selected Exhibition Awards Ceremony - Prizes Presented by Kitashirakawa Wakamiya Prince"</ref><ref>May 25, 1907, Asahi Shimbun: "Naming of Fushimi Wakamiya Royal Daughter"  
Here, "Fushimi Wakamiya" refers to Prince [[:en:Prince Fushimi Hiroyasu|Hiroyasu Fushimi]] before inheriting the [[:en:Fushimi-no-miya|Fushimi-no-miya]] title. He succeeded the title in [[:en:1923|1923]].</ref><ref>December 24, 1941, Yomiuri Shimbun: "Kitashirakawa Wakamiya attends the Children's Music Event"</ref>. According to this custom, Prince [[:en:Prince Tomohito of Mikasa|Tomohito]], the first son of [[:en:Takahito, Prince Mikasa|Prince Takahito of Mikasa]], would be "'''Mikasa Wakamiya'''", and Prince [[:en:Prince Hisahito of Akishino|Hisahito]], the first son of [[:en:Fumihito, Crown Prince of Japan|Prince Fumihito]], would be "'''Akishino Wakamiya'''." However, this designation is rarely used even among those knowledgeable about the [[:en:Imperial House of Japan|Imperial Household]] system today. Instead, it is common to use the {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮号|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyake|qq=}} as if it were a {{ill|surname|ja|名字|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/surname|qq=}}. Prince Tomohito expressed his criticism of this practice. {{main|{{ill|Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|ja|寬仁親王#宮号の有無と表記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|qq=}}}}  

