'''Wakamiya''' (若宮) {{TOCright}}
== Imperial Household == * A child of the {{ill|Imperial Family|ja|皇族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Family|qq=}}. Refers to a {{ill|Imperial Prince|ja|皇子|vi|Hoàng tử|zh|皇子|ko|황자|lt=Imperial Prince|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Prince|qq=}} during their childhood. * Before [[:en:1947|1947]] ({{ill|Shōwa 22|ja|昭和22年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōwa 22|qq=}}), when the [[:en:Ōke|Eleven Miyake]] renounced their {{ill|Imperial status|ja|皇籍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial status|qq=}}, it was customary to refer to the heir of a {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyake|qq=}} head (usually the eldest son) as "'''○○ Wakamiya''' (○○のわかみや)." <ref>May 4, 1895, Yomiuri Shimbun: "The 5th Selected Exhibition Awards Ceremony - Prizes Presented by Kitashirakawa Wakamiya Prince"</ref><ref>May 25, 1907, Asahi Shimbun: "Naming of Fushimi Wakamiya Royal Daughter" Here, "Fushimi Wakamiya" refers to Prince [[:en:Prince Fushimi Hiroyasu|Hiroyasu Fushimi]] before inheriting the [[:en:Fushimi-no-miya|Fushimi-no-miya]] title. He succeeded the title in [[:en:1923|1923]].</ref><ref>December 24, 1941, Yomiuri Shimbun: "Kitashirakawa Wakamiya attends the Children's Music Event"</ref>. According to this custom, Prince [[:en:Prince Tomohito of Mikasa|Tomohito]], the first son of [[:en:Takahito, Prince Mikasa|Prince Takahito of Mikasa]], would be "'''Mikasa Wakamiya'''", and Prince [[:en:Prince Hisahito of Akishino|Hisahito]], the first son of [[:en:Fumihito, Crown Prince of Japan|Prince Fumihito]], would be "'''Akishino Wakamiya'''." However, this designation is rarely used even among those knowledgeable about the [[:en:Imperial House of Japan|Imperial Household]] system today. Instead, it is common to use the {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮号|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyake|qq=}} as if it were a {{ill|surname|ja|名字|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/surname|qq=}}. Prince Tomohito expressed his criticism of this practice. {{main|{{ill|Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|ja|寬仁親王#宮号の有無と表記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|qq=}}}}
== Religion == * A [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shrine]] enshrining the child ({{ill|Mikogami|ja|御子神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikogami|qq=}}) of the main deity ({{ill|Hongen|ja|本宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hongen|qq=}}). Examples include various {{ill|Wakamiya Shrines|ja|若宮神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Shrines|qq=}} and {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrines|ja|若宮八幡宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Hachiman Shrines|qq=}}. * [[:en:Wakamiya Ōji|Wakamiya Ōji]] - The [[:en:Sandō|approach]] to [[:en:Tsurugaoka Hachimangū|Tsurugaoka Hachimangū]] in [[:en:Kamakura|Kamakura]], [[:en:Kanagawa Prefecture|Kanagawa Prefecture]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|若宮神社 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Shrine (disambiguation)|qq=}} * {{ill|Wakamiya Sha (disambiguation)|ja|若宮社 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Sha (disambiguation)|qq=}} * {{ill|Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|若宮八幡宮 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine (disambiguation)|qq=}}
== Place Names == Japanese place names. * Wakamiya (Yamagata City) - A {{ill|locality|ja|地名|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/locality|qq=}} in [[:en:Yamagata (city)|Yamagata City]], [[:en:Yamagata Prefecture|Yamagata Prefecture]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya (Nakano Ward)|ja|若宮 (中野区)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya (Nakano Ward)|qq=}} - A locality in [[:en:Nakano, Tokyo|Nakano Ward]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya (Okegawa City)|ja|若宮 (桶川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya (Okegawa City)|qq=}} - A locality in [[:en:Okegawa, Saitama|Okegawa City]], [[:en:Saitama Prefecture|Saitama Prefecture]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya (Ichikawa City)|ja|若宮 (市川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya (Ichikawa City)|qq=}} - A locality in [[:en:Ichikawa, Chiba|Ichikawa City]], [[:en:Chiba Prefecture|Chiba Prefecture]]. * Wakamiya (Ichihara City) - A locality in [[:en:Ichihara, Chiba|Ichihara City]], Chiba Prefecture. * Wakamiya (Nagano City) - A locality in [[:en:Nagano (city)|Nagano City]], [[:en:Nagano Prefecture|Nagano Prefecture]]. {{main|{{ill|Owabebe (Nagano City)#Wakamiya|ja|尾張部 (長野市)#若宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Owabebe (Nagano City)#Wakamiya|qq=}}}} * {{ill|Wakamiya (Kanazawa City)|ja|若宮 (金沢市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya (Kanazawa City)|qq=}} - A locality in [[:en:Kanazawa|Kanazawa City]], [[:en:Ishikawa Prefecture|Ishikawa Prefecture]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya (Saga City)|ja|若宮 (佐賀市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya (Saga City)|qq=}} - A locality in [[:en:Saga (city)|Saga City]], [[:en:Saga Prefecture|Saga Prefecture]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya (Fukuoka City)|ja|若宮 (福岡市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya (Fukuoka City)|qq=}} - A locality in [[:en:Higashi-ku, Fukuoka|Higashi Ward, Fukuoka City]], [[:en:Fukuoka|Fukuoka City]], [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]]. * [[:en:Wakamiya, Fukuoka|Wakamiya Town]] - A former municipality in [[:en:Kurate District, Fukuoka|Kurate District]], Fukuoka Prefecture, now part of [[:en:Miyawaka|Miyawaka City]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya Town (disambiguation)|ja|若宮町 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Town (disambiguation)|qq=}} * {{ill|Wakamiya Town (Kanazawa City)|ja|若宮町 (金沢市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Town (Kanazawa City)|qq=}} - A locality in Kanazawa City, Ishikawa Prefecture. * {{ill|Wakamiya Town (Nakamura Ward, Nagoya City)|ja|若宮町 (名古屋市中村区)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Town (Nakamura Ward, Nagoya City)|qq=}} - A locality in {{ill|Nakamura Ward, Nagoya City|ja|名古屋市中村区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakamura Ward, Nagoya City|qq=}}, [[:en:Nagoya|Nagoya City]]. * Wakamiya Town (Yamaguchi City) - A locality in [[:en:Yamaguchi (city)|Yamaguchi City]], [[:en:Yamaguchi Prefecture|Yamaguchi Prefecture]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya Village (disambiguation)|ja|若宮村 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Village (disambiguation)|qq=}} * {{ill|Wakamiya Island|ja|若宮島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya Island|qq=}} - An island in [[:en:Iki, Nagasaki|Iki City]], [[:en:Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki Prefecture]]. * {{ill|Wakamiya River|ja|若宮川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamiya River|qq=}} - A {{ill|river|ja|河川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/river|qq=}} in [[:en:Nihonmatsu, Fukushima|Nihonmatsu City]], [[:en:Fukushima Prefecture|Fukushima Prefecture]].
