s designation is rarely used even among those knowledgeable about the [[:en:Imperial House of Japan|Imperial Household]] system today. Instead, it is common to use the {{ill|Miyake|ja|宮号|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyake|qq=|1=miya|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q12250872}} as if it were a {{ill|surname|ja|名字|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/surname|qq=|1=myōji|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q69634220}}. Prince Tomohito expressed his criticism of this practice. {{main|{{ill|Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|ja|寬仁親王#宮号の有無と表記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Tomohito#Miyake naming conventions|qq=|1=Prince Tomohito of Mikasa|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q486381}}}}
